  "id": "trendfollowing_vidya_cmo",
  "name": "VIDYA CMO Trend Confirmation Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm utilizes the Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) to identify trend direction and the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) for momentum confirmation. It employs the Parabolic SAR for trade management, entering long positions when the VIDYA slope is positive and the CMO crosses above zero, while ensuring the price remains above the Parabolic SAR dot.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm using a 4-hour timeframe that combines the Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) with the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) and the Parabolic SAR for trend confirmation and trade management. Entry: go long when VIDYA slope turns positive and CMO crosses above zero, provided the price is above the Parabolic SAR dot. Exit: close long positions when CMO crosses below zero or price closes below the Parabolic SAR. Use a fixed 1.5% trailing stop based on the Parabolic SAR levels. Include volume filter by only entering trades when the volume is above the 20-period Simple Moving Average of volume to avoid low-liquidity periods.",
